9 B. NON-PERIODICAL PERMIT NEWSPAPER: A legal newspaper of the
10 county is any newspaper of general circulation which, during a
11 period of one hundred four (104) consecutive weeks immediately prior
12 to the first publication of such notice, advertisement or
13 publication:
14 1. Has published a printed issue at least once per week;
15 2. Continuously offers paid subscriptions to the general public
16 and maintains a minimum of two hundred (200) paid print
17 subscriptions to individual verified subscribers, and delivers such
18 subscriptions by verified mail or carrier delivery to paid
19 individual subscribers. The cost of a paid subscription shall
20 exceed a nominal fee including the cost of printing and
21 distribution;
22 3. Has averaged a minimum of twenty-five percent (25%) news
23 content over the preceding 12-month period, and news content shall
24 be content generally found in local news publications, such as
